onventional academic curriculum. The book follows Molly Beauregard and her students on their intellectual and spiritual journey over the course of a semester in her class, "Consciousness, Creativity, and Identity." Interweaving personal stories, student writing, and Beauregard's responses, along with recommendations for further reading and a research appendix, it makes the case for the transformative power of consciousness-centered education. Written in a warm, engaging voice that reflects Beauregard's teaching style, Tuning the Student Mind provides an accessible, step-by-step template for other educators, while inviting readers more broadly to reconnect with the joy of learning in and beyond the classroom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAffective educationzUnited States. 0aCollege studentszUnited StatesxPsychology. 0aEducation, HigherxAims and objectiveszUnited States. 0aSelf-consciousness (Awareness)xStudy and teaching (Higher)zUnited States. 0aSelf-consciousness (Awareness)xStudy and teaching (Higher)zUnitedStates. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aEducation : Philosophy of Education. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Contemplative Studies. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847885240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438478852423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438478852/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles